    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "12 of 13 V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency in Test conditions (achieved level 2 versus required level 3) reflects the limitation of the single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration; the review team accepted this gap given that (a) compression-bending is the primary failure mode for this device, (b) all three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria with E/uval well below 1.96, and (c) two-laboratory testing provides cross-laboratory reproducibility evidence. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the intended regulatory decision.",
